Qpex are the innovators of RTP for the mining industry. RTP is the perfect pipe for high pressure liquids and slurries in mines, with outstanding long life reliability. RTP is a thermoplastic pipe with non-metallic inner and outer surfaces, and therefore highly resistant to corrosion and abrasion. The pipe wall of RTP is internally reinforced and designed to sustain very high system pressures. Supplied in continuous lengths on coils or reels, RTP is fast and easy to install on site, without welders or heavy installation machinery and very few joins. PEX cross-linked polyethelyene pipe is designed specically for mining industry applications. With remarkable resistance to abrasion and high temperature, PEX pipe is widely recognized as one of the toughest pipe materials in the world, It is the best pipe material to prevent scale buildup having very low absolute surface roughness of only 0.0005mm. The anti crack propogation properties of PEX and its total resistance to UV degradation, combined with its wear resistance mean that PEX pipe can be dragged for long distances across rocky ground and installed permanently overland. It is easily cut to length and joined on site without specialist equipment or training. With its high tensile strength, PEX pipe is often used for pumps in boreholes or hung down open cut pits. The versatility, strength and exibility of PEX pipe is unrivalled. LINED SLURRY PIPELINES OVERVIEW Internally lined metallic or GRP pipelines from Qpex are made for highly abrasive slurry, and high pressure applications. These pipes provide exceptional wear life and far outlast steel. Qpex Lined slurry pipelines are designed on a project-by-project basis. Qpex supply lined slurry pipelines in steel or GRP, with a large range of pipe diameters. There are multiple liner material options and thicknesses that can be varied depending on the application, and media being transferred. Qpex supply the worlds rst, site weldable lined steel pipeline system. This design enables a lined steel pipe to be welded together on site without damaging the lining material, avoiding the need for bolted anges or other special connections. Qpex also supply a wide range of valves and instrumentation for slurry pipelines including plug valves, knifegate valves, 3-way valves, density meters, ow and pressure transmitters, gaskets, pipe brackets and more... Lined Chemical Pipes Qpex supply a comprehensive range of PTFE, PFA, PVDF and PP lined pipes for high temperature and corrosive applications. Lined pipes combine the superior chemical resistance of the liner material with the structural strength of the pipe outer (steel or resin pipe).They are ideal for extremely aggressive and corrosive chemicals at temperatures up to 230C. Lined pipes and ttings are all supplied with integral anges. Pipe spools usually have 1 xed and 1 slip ange. Fittings, like elbows, tees, reducers, instrument tees, and valves are usually all supplied with xed anges only. All lined pipes and valves are manufactured in full accordance with International Standards. Our PTFE, PFA, PVDF and PP liner options, are oered with steel and stainless steel pipe externals or a special type of resin pipe. Plastic Pipes Qpex also supply full plastic pipe options in PVDF, C-PVC and ECTFE material in both single and double wall options. These pipes have a full range of matching ttings and connections for butt weld, solvent weld, and socket weld options. They are widely used for chemical processing with reagents like acids and solvents. A complete range of plastic pipe installation accessories and adaptors like pipe brackets and welding equipment are also available. Qpex are industry leaders in Fire Resistant, Anti-Static (FRAS) rated non-metallic pipes that are designed for use in hazardous coal mining applications. Our FRAS pipe is supplied in both lower pressure non-reinforced and higher pressure reinforced versions. FRAS pipe is supplied by Qpex in a large selection of diameters and lengths, and a choice of end connection types. These pipes are safe to use in mines which have exposure to all classes of methane and coal dust hazards. UNDERGROUND SUPPORT SYSTEMS OVERVIEW Qpex oer an innovative development in support systems for underground mines. Our patented Mimesh Composite mesh lining is specically designed to protect ceilings and side walls in underground excavations. MiMesh sheets are rigid, resilient and exible. Compared with steel mesh, MiMesh has excellent strength parameters yet is 3 times lighter. Unlike steel, MiMesh is non-corrodable and does not require periodic replacement. MiMesh is also certied non-combustible and anti-static product (FRAS), a preferred product in hazardous coal mines. All variants of MiMesh are available with additional FRAS fabric, where the mesh grid holes are completely lled. Qpex also supply underground piping support accessories for tunnels and shafts including Gewi bars, pipe clamp brackets, chair supports and piping connectors to accomodate specic site conditions and requirements. HEAT EXCHANGERS OVERVIEW Qpex oer a full range of advanced design Heat Exchangers for mining and mineral processing in a variety of applications including abrasive slurries, high viscousity liquids, and corrosive chemicals. One of our key HX products in shell and tube designs is the patented KICC corrugated tube technology that signicantly increases the eciency and cleanability, and reduces the unit size and cost. We also supply specialised spiral heat exchangers with access doors are ideal for slurries and solid laden mixtures that tend to block or foul in other heat exchanger designs. Qpex also supply plate and shell heat exchangers from the pioneer and market leader in this technology. The core of these ultra compact and highly ecient heat exchangers is a fully welded pack enclosed in a strong shell structure, which eliminates the need for a gasket. Sizes available are amongst the largest in the world with eective heating / cooling areas up to 4000m. A full range of wetted material options are available, including specialist steel and alloys, as well as graphite and silicon carbide.
